Self-compassion & SDO Study

Polina Beloborodova

10/12/2020

Sample

The data were collected from 839 students of the University of Hawaiʻi at Mānoa in the Spring (N = 81) and Fall (N = 460) semesters of 2019, as well as Fall semester of 2020 (N = 298). Participants’ age ranged from 17 to 55 (M = 20.1, SD = 4.09). Participants self-identified as female (71.28%), male (28.25%), and other gender (4 persons). Self-reported ethnicity was distributed as follows: Asian (42.79%), White (non-Hispanic, 23.6%), Multicultural (17.16%), Hawaiian/Pacific Islander (6.44%), Hispanic (5.48%), Other (2.15%), Black (non-Hispanic, 1.55%), and Native American (7 persons).
